The paper proposes a computer-aided detection (CAD) system for mammographic masses using deep learning and image processing techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging (cs.MM) and uses transfer learning with a state-of-the-art deep learning framework (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its method using metrics such as true positive rate and Dice similarity index, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR).
